President Reagan was meeting thisafternoon with his top economic advisers on developments in thestock market and the White House said he would issue astatement at 1700 EDT.    Spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said Reagan met in the WhiteHouse residence shortly after the market closed with TreasurySecretary James Baker, Federal Reserve Board Chairman AlanGreenspan, Chairman Beryl Sprinkel of the President's Councilof Economic Advisers and chief of staff Howard Baker.    Reagan scrubbed a reception for Republican presidentialcandidates to make room in his schedule for the meeting. Reuter&#3;